{
  "name": "Bhai Gurmukh Singh (USA / Jalandhar)",
  "url": "https://kirtansewa.net/index.php/bhai-gurmukh-singh-usa-jalandhar/",
  "image_url": "https://cdn.kirtansewa.net/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/21221929/Bhai-Gurmukh-Singh-Jalandhar-son-of-Bhai-Bahadur-Singh-1.jpg",
  "body": [
    "Bhai Gurmukh Singh Ji, born on April 13, 1947, in the city of Khanewal, now part of Pakistan, was the son of Bibi Beant Kaur Ji and the esteemed Kirtani Sant Bahadur Singh Ji. Renowned for his classical Kirtan, Sant Bahadur Singh Ji performed Kirtan in the ‘Sangat’ of Sant Baba Nand Singh Ji of Nanaksar, for most of his life.",
    "From an early age, Bhai Gurmukh Singh Ji was deeply immersed in the tradition of Kirtan, accompanying his father on the Tanpura and developing a voice that harmoniously complemented Sant Bahadur Singh Ji’s singing.",
    "In 1965, Bhai Gurmukh Singh Ji and Sant Bahadur Singh Ji embarked on an extensive international tour, bringing their Kirtan to the ‘Sangat’ across Africa, Singapore, Thailand, England, Italy, Afghanistan, Iraq, and the United States. Their performances captivated and inspired many.",
    "Bhai Gurmukh Singh Ji was recognized for his musical excellence with numerous awards from the Punjab Government and the Central Government in various Kirtan competitions. He settled in New York, USA, where he resided until his passing in 2011. Although he is no longer with us, his legacy endures through his recordings, preserving the beauty of his melodious voice for future generations.",
    "If anyone has more recordings or photos of Bhai Gurmukh Singh Ji to share, please contact us."
  ],
